<!-- DynamoDB Primary Key -->
<section id="aws-properties-dynamodb-provisionedthroughput" role="topic">
   <title id="aws-properties-dynamodb-provisionedthroughput.title">DynamoDB Provisioned Throughput</title>

   <para>Describes a set of provisioned throughput values for an <link linkend="aws-resource-dynamodb-table"
         endterm="aws-resource-dynamodb-table.title"/> resource. &DDB; uses these capacity units to allocate
      sufficient resources to provide the requested throughput.</para>

   <para>For a complete discussion of &DDB; provisioned throughput values, see <ulink
         url="http://&domain;/amazondynamodb/2011-12-05/developerguide/WorkingWithDDTables.html#ProvisionedThroughput"
      >Specifying Read and Write Requirements (Provisioned Throughput)</ulink> in the <citetitle>&DDB; Developer Guide</citetitle>.</para>

   <section condition="json">
      <title>Syntax</title>
      <programlisting>
{
   "<link linkend="cfn-dynamodb-provisionedthroughput-readcapacityunits">ReadCapacityUnits</link>" : <replaceable>Number</replaceable>,
   "<link linkend="cfn-dynamodb-provisionedthroughput-writecapacityunits">WriteCapacityUnits</link>" : <replaceable>Number</replaceable>
}</programlisting>
   </section>
	
	<section condition="yaml">
		<title>Syntax</title>
		<programlisting><link linkend="cfn-dynamodb-provisionedthroughput-readcapacityunits">ReadCapacityUnits</link>: <replaceable>Number</replaceable>
<link linkend="cfn-dynamodb-provisionedthroughput-writecapacityunits">WriteCapacityUnits</link>: <replaceable>Number</replaceable></programlisting>
	</section>

   <section>
      <title>Parameters</title>
      <variablelist>
         <varlistentry id="cfn-dynamodb-provisionedthroughput-readcapacityunits">
            <term>ReadCapacityUnits</term>
            <listitem>
               <para>Sets the desired minimum number of consistent reads of items (of up to 1KB in size) per second for
                  the specified table before Amazon DynamoDB balances the load.</para>
               <para><emphasis>Required</emphasis>: Yes</para>
               <para><emphasis>Type</emphasis>: Number</para>
            </listitem>
         </varlistentry>
         <varlistentry id="cfn-dynamodb-provisionedthroughput-writecapacityunits">
            <term>WriteCapacityUnits</term>
            <listitem>
               <para>Sets the desired minimum number of consistent writes of items (of up to 1KB in size) per second for
                  the specified table before Amazon DynamoDB balances the load.</para>
            </listitem>
         </varlistentry>
      </variablelist>
      <note>
         <para>For detailed information about the limits of provisioned throughput values in &DDB;, see <ulink
               url="http://&domain;/amazondynamodb/2011-12-05/developerguide/Limits.html">Limits in
               Amazon DynamoDB</ulink> in the <citetitle>&DDB; Developer Guide</citetitle>.</para>
      </note>
   </section>

   <section>
      <title>Examples</title>
      <para>For an example of declared provisioned throughput values, see <link linkend="aws-resource-dynamodb-table"
            endterm="aws-resource-dynamodb-table.title"/>.</para>
   </section>
</section>
